I'm disheartened by Pakistan's loss in the T20 cricket World Cup 2026 match against India. It's just a game, and wins and losses are part of it. However, when losing becomes a recurring pattern for a nation, that's when the problem arises. The current hybrid political system, where both politicians and the army hold power but are unaccountable, is a major issue. False promises are made to the public, and this system only breeds corruption. The people are frustrated and have lost hope. 
In my opinion, Imran Khan is the only true leader Pakistan has had. He instilled confidence in his team during the World Cup, and they went on to win. As the Prime Minister of Pakistan, he made the public believe in their potential, and they achieved success. 
Pakistan was created with the hope of providing a fair and prosperous life for Muslims, free from discrimination. However, corrupt power has its own agenda, serving personal interests and exploiting the public. The history of dictatorships and the separation of East Pakistan are testaments to this. 
The moral of the story is that Pakistan needs either an honest dictator or a leader like Imran Khan.
